Chicken Caesar Smash Tacos
  --Lindsay, Pinch of Yum

Sauce:
1/2 c mayo
1/4 c plain yogurt
1 tbsp Dijon
1 tbsp Worcestershire sauce
1 tbsp lemon juice
1 clove garlic, grated
salt to taste

Whisk sauce ingredients until smooth.

Salad:
1/2 head romaine, finely shredded (2–3 c)
1/2 c pepperoncini, sliced
1/4 c freshly grated Parmesan cheese

Toss romaine, pepperoncini, parmesan, and about half of the Caesar sauce until well-combined. (For the remaining sauce – whisk it with 1-2 tbsp of water to make it smoother for dunking.)
  
Tacos:
1 lb ground chicken
1 tbsp Trader Joe’s aglio olio seasoning, or any chicken seasoning
salt and pepper to taste
6–8 small flour tortillas (eg La Banderita “Street Taco” tortillas)
avocado oil for frying

Mix the seasoning into the ground chicken. Place your tortillas on a large cutting board or tray; spread each tortilla with some of the ground chicken mixture, pushing it all the way to the edges or even slightly past. Heat a thin layer of oil over medium heat (2 tbsp or more will give you the best crispy crust). Working in batches, place the tortilla chicken-side down and press down with a spatula for 15-30 s. Cook for another 2-3 min until the chicken is browned and fully cooked. Flip to the other side for another min to get a bit of crisping on the back side of the tortilla. Remove tacos from skillet and fold in half (the tortilla may crackle a bit when you fold them – that’s fine!). If needed, place on a baking sheet and pop in a warm oven until you’re ready to serve. When you’re ready to eat, stuff the Caesar salad inside the tacos! Serve alongside a dish of the remaining Caesar sauce for dipping.
  

Note: can use store bought caesar dressing
